  "2026-03-05T13:05:50.978Z",maintainer-agent,Why this exists semantic mutation refresh skips missing IDs and delete flows can leave stale vector records
  "2026-03-05T13:06:04.251Z",maintainer-agent,"Planned change-set docs first: clarify semantic mutation refresh delete behavior in PRD and README, then implement vector-store delete execution and missing-ID refresh pruning with deterministic warnings plus targeted/unit regression tests."
  "2026-03-05T13:07:11.485Z",maintainer-agent,"Docs-first update complete: PRD and README now explicitly require mutation refresh to prune vectors for missing or deleted affected IDs while preserving deterministic warning behavior on failures."
  "2026-03-05T13:09:56.362Z",maintainer-agent,"Implemented code changes: added vector delete plan/execution in src/core/search/vector-stores.ts and wired src/core/search/cache.ts mutation refresh to prune missing IDs via best-effort vector deletes while keeping deterministic warning/skip behavior for failures."
  "2026-03-05T13:09:56.589Z",maintainer-agent,Added regression coverage in tests/unit/vector-store-adapter.spec.ts for build/execute delete behavior and in tests/unit/search-cache.spec.ts for successful missing-ID prune plus deterministic prune-failure warnings.
  "2026-03-05T13:33:15.768Z",maintainer-agent,"Evidence: pm test pm-fdla --run --timeout 3600 --json passed all linked tests (coverage + targeted search-cache + targeted vector-store-adapter). Regression sweeps passed: pm test-all --status in_progress --timeout 3600 --json => items=1 linked_tests=3 passed=3 failed=0 skipped=0; pm test-all --status closed --timeout 3600 --json => items=71 linked_tests=218 passed=59 failed=0 skipped=159 deterministic dedupe. Coverage proof from linked coverage command remains 100% lines/branches/functions/statements (All files 100/100/100/100). Follow-up items created: none."
